<p>Though its Nigerian business is profitable, currency depreciation pressured KingMakers’ operations. The broader company, including Nigeria and South Africa, <a href="https://webstir.jse.co.za/Downloads/File/?id=%2fZGoH%2fXB6Psvwftx6cQ%2fmw%3d%3d" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">recorded $34 million loss after tax</a> in 2025.</p>



