<p>MultiChoice realised years ago that its 41-year-old legacy TV business needed anchors to survive. It has since built an ecosystem that looks like this: a new subscriber can either pay for DStv services with or without the decoder; make MultiChoice-related payments using Moment; insure their decoder; stream content using DStv Internet, its fixed wireless access (FWA) service; and earn an extra bit of income betting on their favourite sports teams, all as part of entertainment value-added services.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Canal+, no stranger to this kind of play, will see a reason to bundle content, connectivity, and financial services for the same consumer.&nbsp;</p>
